gomodel:SYNGO_2244  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Absence of the delayed mGluR1-dependent Ca2+ transient in dl20J/dl20J PN spines and hypothetical models for how myosin-Va might function to localize the ER Ca2+ store to spines\"\nFig.2: \"The translocation of ER into spines is disrupted in dl20J/dl20J PNs\"\nFig.3: \"mGFP-myosin-Va expressed in dl20J/dl20J PNs rescues ER targeting and accumulates at the tip of the spine ER\"\nFig.4: \"Myosin-Va is present at the leading tip of the ER tubule as the organelle translocates into a spine\"\n\nFinal implementation:\n'establishment of endoplasmic reticulum localization to postsynapse (GO:0099089)'\npart_of 'regulation of postsynaptic cytosolic calcium levels (GO:0099566)'. Experimental description: - \"Parasagittal slices (250 μm thick) were cut from the cerebellar vermis of dv/dl20J or dl20J/dl20J mice at ....\"\n- Overexpressed protien is of mouse species: \". Plasmids pL7-mGFP-myosin-Va and pL7-mCherry-Myosin-Va correspond to pL7-mGFP and pL7-mCherry, respectively, which contain (in frame and downstream of mGFP or mCherry) the cDNA encoding the full-length, WT, brain-spliced isoform43 of mouse myosin-Va\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2244" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

